name: Baked Red Cabbage Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.75 cup olive oil (save 1/2 cup to serve)

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200Â°C. Line a large baking tray with baking paper. Slice cabbage into 2cm-thick slices from top to base. Arrange on tray.

Combine oil, sugar, garlic, paprika, mint and zest. Brush liberally on both sides of cabbage slices. Bake for 20 minutes, then turn slices and bake for a further 20 minutes or until tender and crisp. Transfer to a platter, sprinkle with dukkah and a little extra oil.
